WAMR's zephyr/module.yml sets kconfig-ext without shipping a Kconfig;
Zephyr west then fails module discovery. Point at a tiny stub Kconfig
instead (Metal wires WAMR from src/zephyr/CMakeLists.txt via
runtime_lib.cmake). Formerly created by scripts/setup-west.sh sed/cat
— now a tracked patch. See docs/SOURCETREE.md "Vendoring".

diff --git a/zephyr/module.yml b/zephyr/module.yml
index 059c7368..8ef7dac7 100644
--- a/zephyr/module.yml
+++ b/zephyr/module.yml
@@ -2,4 +2,4 @@ name: wasm-micro-runtime
 
 build:
   cmake-ext: True
-  kconfig-ext: True
+  kconfig: Kconfig
diff --git a/Kconfig b/Kconfig
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..e69de29b
--- /dev/null
+++ b/Kconfig
@@ -0,0 +1,2 @@
+# WAMR is wired from src/zephyr/CMakeLists.txt (runtime_lib.cmake).
+
